summary:
The Security Council:

1. Endorses the report of the Secretary-General on UNIFIL of 20 January (S/2005/36);
2. Decides to extend the present mandate of UNIFIL until 31 July 2005;
3. Reiterates its strong support for Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty and political independence within its internationally recognized boundaries;
4. Calls upon the Government of Lebanon to fully extend and exercise its authority throughout the south, including through deployment of sufficient Lebanese armed and security forces;
5. Calls on the parties to ensure UNIFIL has full freedom of movement and to report any obstruction;
6. Reiterates its call on the parties to respect the withdrawal line, exercise restraint and cooperate with the UN and UNIFIL;
7. Condemns acts of violence, including recent incidents across the Blue Line, and urges parties to end violations and refrain from provocations;
8. Supports UNIFIL's efforts to maintain the ceasefire through patrols and contacts with parties;
9. Welcomes UNIFIL's contribution to mine clearance, encourages further assistance and commends donor countries;
10. Requests the Secretary-General to continue consultations and report on implementation, UNIFIL activities and UNTSO tasks.
The Security Council:
- Intends to review UNIFIL's mandate and structures at the end of the present mandate, and requests the Secretary-General to provide recommendations, following consultations, including with the Lebanese Government, taking into account the situation on the ground and the Force's activities and contribution to restoring international peace and security;
- Looks forward to the early fulfilment of UNIFIL's mandate;
- Stresses the importance of achieving a comprehensive, just and lasting peace in the Middle East, based on its relevant resolutions, including resolutions 242 (1967) and 338 (1973).
